title: For Sale:  German DWM Commercial Luger, .30 Luger
postcontent:
Up for sale is a DWM Commerical Luger chambered in .30 Luger. It was made sometime in the early 1920's between the world wars by DWM for export to the American market. It has non-matching serial numbers on the parts. The pistol was refinshed at some point but mechanically it works brilliantly, shoots like new with very strong rifling in the barrel and is accurate. The magazine is aftermarket and the toggle link doesn't always lock open on the empty magazine due to damage on the feed lips but it's easy to find an aftermarket replacement. title: For Sale:  Exceptional Pre War Post War Ace Original Box 99% Collector Grade Box Papers Target Letter Scarce!
postcontent: 1947 Colt Pre War Post War Ace. Also included is the original box numbered to the gun with the manual, shooting suggestions pamphlet, and even the test target. It has the correct two tone magazine. These are the rarest of all Aces. There were approximately 200 made after the war entirely out of pre war parts. It would be another 40 years before Colt produced another Ace. Per the Colt Archive letter it was shipped May 9, 1947 to New York, New York. This is a collector grade gun. The finish retains a beautiful dark shine throughout. You will see light handling when you examine the pictures closely but it is all minor with nothing that really stands out. Overall it rates 99%. The bore is bright and shiny. The recoil shield is very clean and shows little use. The trigger has a crisp clean break to it. All of the checkering on the grips is sharp. The right grip has some oil stain discoloration. This one has it all. Condition, completeness, and rarity. It will enhance any advanced collection.

Ergonomics of the grip have been improved by interchangeable backstraps and side panel inserts. In combination with the ambidextrous operating controls, this pistol can be individually adapted to almost any user. No compromises have been made regarding safety. The P30 V2 features the LEM (Law Enforcement Modification) trigger system. With the V2 LEM every trigger pull breaks at the same weight: 7.5-8lbs. Its advanced loaded chamber indicator, which is easily seen and felt, positively indicates a loaded chamber. title: For Sale:  Semi-Auto Sniper Rifle W/ Lps-4x Scope..
postcontent: Here's a Romanian PSL-54C semi-automatic rifle. Sometimes called the "FPK Dragunov", this weapon was designed to engage targets that were out of range for the standard infantry rifle. It is chambered for the powerful 7.62x54R cartridge and wears a 24.4" barrel with chrome lined 4-groove bore and 1/12.5 twist. It is a closely related to the RPK and has a thick walled receiver with reinforced trunnion. The action is pure Kalashnikov, just scaled up for the heavier cartridge. The corrugated steel buttplate is spring dampened to help absorb recoil. All serial numbered parts are matching with the exception of the fire-control components (hammer, sear, selector). The rifle is in very good condition with some handling wear including some minor scratches to the matte black finish. There is no rust or pitting. The stocks are in very good shape with some normal handling wear, dents and small scuffs...but no cracks or chips. The rifle appear to be in good mechanical condition and the bore is in good shape as well. It comes complete with the correct/very good condition LPS-4x Type 2 scope with ranging reticle. The scope attaches to the left side receiver rail with a quick detach mount. One 10-round magazine is included. This rifle should be lots of fun to shoot!

postcontent: Available today is a used Remington Sportsman 48.  12ga semi auto with 3 round capacity. Here is your chance to own a piece of American hunting history. The Sportsman '48 is a variation introduced to comply with various US hunting laws that limited shotguns used for hunting to three shells. It came with a crimped magazine tube that allowed it to be loaded with only two shells in the magaizine. One Additional round placed in the chamber brought its total to three rounds. I'm happy to answer any questions you might have and supply you with more pictures.Price is 0.5 Ethereum.
